common C syntax errors-
 1. missing Semicolons(;) or Brackets()
 2. equality operator( = )and( == )
 3. declare prototype for function before main.
 4. missing header file.
 5. character constant and character string
    t='a'; t is a character variable.  
    t="a"; (wrong declaration it should be t[]="a") t is a pointer variable for char.
 6. exceding the limits of array. (Memory Exception)
 7. forgeting to reserve an extra locaton for an array.
 8. forgetting an ampersand before nonpointer variable.(sacanf)
 9. using variable before declaration.
10. for break in switch case.
11. no Semicolon is needed for declaration of constants using #define.